OL,4,Ccar as a weapon' to murder fiance
OL,6,FBut Wood told the court that when she
OL,7,Fdrove Mr Watson home from the party in
OL,8,Fhis car, despite knowing she was over
OL,9,Fthe drink-drive limit, he "flipped"
OL,10,Fand accused her of flirting with other
OL,11,Fmen.
OL,13,FThe student described an argument
OL,14,Fwhich continued when they returned to
OL,15,Fthe house they owned in Oak Street.
OL,17,FShe told the court she went out to her
OL,18,Fcar to leave but Mr Watson followed.
