OL,6,FOfficers attended and spoke to Wood,
OL,7,Fsubsequently arresting her due to the
OL,8,Fdisclosures she had made.
OL,10,FShe also failed a roadside breath test
OL,11,Fand was found to have 61 micrograms of
OL,12,Falcohol per 100 millilitres of breath,
OL,13,Fover the legal limit of 35. Upon
OL,14,Farrest she told officers; "it's fine,
OL,15,FI deserve it".
OL,17,FWoods was arrested on suspicion of
OL,18,Fmurder and interviewed by the police.
OL,19,FThough she made no comment in the
OL,20,Finterviews, she admitted guilt on
OL,21,Fmultiple occasions.
